  "prompt": "Does the English East India Company (trading) still exist?",
  "response": "The English East India Company, originally established in 1600, no longer exists as a trading entity. It was dissolved in 1874 after losing its administrative powers in India to the British Crown following the Indian Rebellion of 1857. However, the name \"East India Company\" has been revived by various modern businesses that use it for branding and selling products, particularly those related to tea and spices. These modern companies are not connected to the original East India Company and operate independently.",
